function Start(idActorPlayer, idActorGizmo)

	--Enable all the spawners. Wave timers are controlled on the spawners themselves.	
	for i, idAllSpawner in ipairs(tAllSpawners) do
		if Hydra.ActorIsValid then 
			Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idAllSpawner, false)
		end
	end
	
	--Add a VFX buff to the statue.
	for i, idStatue in ipairs(tStatues) do
		Hydra.Wait(0.15)
		Hydra.BuffApplyToTarget(S_CHARGING_POWER, "STATUE_CHARGING", idStatue)
	end
	
end

function Start(idActorKiller, szGroup)

-- Change the statues back to their default look.
	for i, idStatue in ipairs(tStatues) do
		Hydra.Wait(0.15)
		Hydra.BuffApplyToTarget(S_CHARGING_POWER, "STATUE_LOOK_SWITCH_OFF", idStatue)
	end
	
-- Enable reward chest.	
	if Hydra.ActorIsValid(idChest) then
		Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idChest, false)
	end

end

function Start()

	-- Disable spawners
	for i, idAllSpawner in ipairs(tAllSpawners) do
		if Hydra.ActorIsValid(idAllSpawner) then
			Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idAllSpawner, true)
		end
	end
	
end

function Start(idActorSpawned, idActorSpawner)

--Setting the count for the number of elites killed.
nEliteCount = nEliteCount + 1

end

	Hydra.SetGameVariableNumeric("DE_ChestRewardRare", 1)

unk_28bc3c5.value:
function Start(idActorKiller, idActorKilled)
	
	--Checking the distance from the center to determine if the monster is killed in the blood circle.
	--Any monsters killed inside the circle have an extra blood effect.
	if Hydra.ActorDistanceSquaredBetweenActors(idSelf, idActorKilled) <= N_QUEST_CREDIT_MAX_RADIUS_SQ then 
		Hydra.ActorSetPowerEffectSize(idActorKilled, 4)
		Hydra.ActorPlayEffectGroup(idActorKilled, S_BLOOD_EXPLOSION_FX)
		
		-- Award points based on monster difficulty.
		if Hydra.ActorIsInGroup(idActorKilled, S_SMALL_POINT_MONSTERS) then
			nBloodProgress =  nBloodProgress + N_MONSTER_POINTS_SMALL
		elseif Hydra.ActorIsInGroup(idActorKilled, S_LARGE_POINT_MONSTERS) then
			nBloodProgress = nBloodProgress + N_MONSTER_POINTS_LARGE
		end
		
		--Caps nBloodProgress to 100 if greater than 100 (FEN-601202)
		if nBloodProgress > 100 then
			nBloodProgress = 100
		end
	end
	
	-- Set the chargeable progress based on points earned from monsters.
	for i, idStatue in ipairs(tStatues) do
		idBlood = Hydra.ActorsLinkedByActor(idStatue)[1]
		Hydra.ChargeableGizmoSetProgress(idBlood, nBloodProgress)
	end
	
	-- When the chargeable fills up, spawn an elite.
	if nBloodProgress >= 100 and nEliteCount == 0 then
		if Hydra.ActorIsValid(idElite01) then
			Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idElite01, false)
			
			--Resetting the chargeable.
			for i, idStatue in ipairs(tStatues) do
				idBlood = Hydra.ActorsLinkedByActor(idStatue)[1]
				nBloodProgress = 0
				Hydra.ChargeableGizmoSetProgress(idBlood, nBloodProgress)
			end
		end
		
	-- Spawning the second elite.	
	elseif nBloodProgress >= 100 and nEliteCount == 1 then
		if Hydra.ActorIsValid(idElite02) then
			Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idElite02, false)
		end
	end

end

function Start(idActorSpawned, idActorSpawner)

	--Adding some blood VFX when the elites spawn.
	Hydra.ActorSetPowerEffectSize(idActorSpawned, 4)
	Hydra.ActorPlayEffectGroup(idActorSpawned, S_BLOOD_SPAWN_FX)

end

unk_993f312.value:
-- ======= CONSTANTS =======
	N_QUEST_CREDIT_MAX_RADIUS = 3.5
	N_QUEST_CREDIT_MAX_RADIUS_SQ = math.pow(N_QUEST_CREDIT_MAX_RADIUS, 2) -- square it once, never have to do math again
	N_MONSTER_POINTS_SMALL = 5
	N_MONSTER_POINTS_LARGE = 10
	
	
-- ======= VARIABLES =======	
	nEliteCount = 0
	nBloodProgress = 0
